        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 12:39PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1239 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Glencoe, or near Hokes Bluff, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gadsden, Jacksonville, Piedmont, Hokes Bluff, Glencoe, Weaver,
Jacksonville State University, Southside, Knightens Crossroads, Cobb
City, Sulphur Springs, Reaves, and Wellington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
